reviews.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on August 3, 2020
reviews.name: k dorney
reviews.title: Overall a good machine. Just a few items that make me unhappy.
reviews.review: My three issues with this system are:1. It only has a 100M network card. That is slow in today's world when 1Gig is common.2. The microphone is not very responsive. We use it with Zoom and it does not pickup up very well or very quickly.3. The battery is really undersized. You get a few hours of use before plugging in. I bought a power brick to help.I question whether I should have moved up to the business oriented Dell laptop to avoid the issues above, but the extra $1000 or so for one of those makes putting up with these issues ok.

reviews.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on June 24, 2020
reviews.name: lmelton
reviews.title: this is the worst laptop I have owned
reviews.review: I have bought Commodore, Epson, Apple, HP and Toshiba.This is substandard.There are other cheap laptops with better performance.Mine is a Inspiron 15 5000 series that has cost me time and money since the warranty expired.I will not pay another dollar to fix it.All of us hate frozen cursors which may be a Windows 10 issue but power and earphone issues are Dell.In the past when Windows locked up, I could disconnect the battery and reboot.Can't do it with this one.There is no battery access.I have to disconnect the power and wait for the battery to run down.

reviews.title: Secure
reviews.review: I used to using Mac until I found this version. I like to using Dell with window system, which is easier for daily work. System is very secure, every time when I download something from the website, system automatically runs a scan for the item to make sure it is safe to download. Oh, and there was a free mouse which works great! I am not a computer man, but I love working with this computer.
